Title : Felix Dreyschock
Text : [[File:Felix Dreyschock SMT 1889.jpg|thumb|Felix Dreyschock. [[Xylography]] 1889.]]
'''Felix Dreyschock''' (27 December 1860 in [[Leipzig]] &ndash; 1 August 1906 in [[Berlin]]) was a German pianist, nephew of [[Alexander Dreyschock]].<ref name="Runeberg">{{cite book | url=http://runeberg.org/nfbf/0461.html | title=Nordisk familjebok | publisher=Project Runeberg | pages=853â€“854}}</ref> He was a pupil of [[Friedrich Kiel]], [[Wilhelm Taubert]] and [[Heinrich Ehrlich]] in Berlin,<ref name="The music dictionary">{{cite web | url=http://themusicdictionary.org/ehrlich-alfred-heinrich/ | title=Ehrlich, Alfred Heinrich | publisher=The Grove Dictionary of Music & Musicians | accessdate=2014-05-03}}</ref> where he in 1883 began to give concerts.<ref name="Runeberg"/> In Stockholm he performed successfully in 1886 and 1889, both as a virtuoso and composer. He wrote major and minor works for [[piano]], [[violin]], vocals, [[orchestra]], etc.

